{"questionId":"14588687","questionHtml":"<p>The graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> is obtained from the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> by a horizontal stretch with scale factor&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>, followed by a vertical translation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> units.</p>\n<p>Find the value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>(accept translate/shift 3 (units) down)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14588687","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ2.3b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The graph of g is obtained from the graph of f by a horizontal stretch with scale factor k, followed by a vertical translation of c units. Find the value of k and the value of c.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Quadratic function"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}